									<img src="https://3.files.edl.io/bba0/20/04/14/204806-4df77dd3-9189-49ac-adfe-19f213864479.png" alt="TEXQUEST"></a>
							<p>
								Excellent Reading Resources
							</p>
						</section></article><article id="hp_news_article_4" class="cf" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Article"><header class="cf"><h1 class="title" itemprop="name headline" id="hp_news_article_4_title">
		<a href="/apps/news/article/1207584">
								CISD Meal Pickup
							</a>
						</h1>
					</header><section class="summary cf" itemprop="description" aria-labelledby="hp_news_article_4_title"><p>
								There will be no CISD meal pickups Friday, April 10 or Monday, April 13
							</p>
						</section></article><article id="hp_news_article_5" class="cf" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Article"><header class="cf"><h1 class="title" itemprop="name headline" id="hp_news_article_5_title">
		<a href="/apps/news/article/1200358">
								Superintendent Update April 1, 2020
							</a>
						</h1>
					</header><section class="summary cf" itemprop="description" aria-labelledby="hp_news_article_5_title"><p>
								Comfort ISD Update April 1, 2020<br><br>Given the rapidly evolving situation with COVID-19, Comfort ISD will extend the suspension of normal district operations through May 4, 2020, in an effort to support our nation’s need to slow the spread of the novel coronavirus or COVID-19.
							</p>
						</section></article><article id="hp_news_article_6" class="cf" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Article"><header class="cf"><h1 class="title" itemprop="name headline" id="hp_news_article_6_title">
		<a href="/apps/news/article/1200354">
								CISD Meal Pickup Changes
							</a>
						</h1>
					</header><section class="summary cf" itemprop="description" aria-labelledby="hp_news_article_6_title"><p>
								To reduce the necessary number of pickups, CISD meal pickup will be from 8:30 to 10:30 AM Monday, Wednesday and Friday. Monday and Wednesday any child in the car will receive 2 breakfast and 2 lunch and 1 breakfast and 1 lunch on Friday.
							</p>
						</section></article><article id="hp_news_article_7" class="cf" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Article"><header class="cf"><h1 class="title" itemprop="name headline" id="hp_news_article_7_title">
		<a href="/apps/news/article/1194890">
								Comfort ISD offers breakfast and lunch for anyone under 18 yrs old starting March 24.
							</a>
						</h1>
					</header><section class="summary cf" itemprop="description" aria-labelledby="hp_news_article_7_title"><p>
								Starting tomorrow, March 24, Comfort ISD will providing breakfast and lunch at Comfort Elementary School via a drive thru only service at the normal parent pick-up area on 4th Street at the back of the school. Breakfast will be from 7:30 - 8:30 AM. Lunch will be 11:30 AM - 12:30 PM. Any person 18 and under can receive a meal but they must be present at pick-up. To follow social distancing guidelines, you must remain in your car.
							</p>
						</section></article><a href="/apps/news/category/2783" class="read-more-link">Show All News »</a>

